race.comment: ISLA'S FURY (7) is a lightly raced mare resuming from a long spell. Beaten just a neck at her only run last time in and presents fitter for a trial. Has ability and good speed. Should go close this line-up off the inside. BOLD STARLET (9) got well back on debut and turned there, but did find the line well without threatening. Sure to be improved and can run on into the frame. ALL KYOTO (1) resumes from a long break. Yet to hit the placings but trialling well for return and can run a race at odds. ARIZONA WILDFIRE (4) is a first starter by Anders and from the stakes-winning mare Heat Of The Fire. From a good family of winners and worth watching for any market moves after a solid trial.
